Package com.chillycheesy.modulo.commands.operator.natif

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AliasOperator
    Operator that replace an alias with their values, like a variable Exemple: ewokName = Wicket
    AndOperator
    Operator that return true if the left and right parameter are true, false in any other case.
    BlockOperator  
    CommandStatusOperator  
    CreateAliasOperator  
    CreateStrictAliasOperator  
    DivideOperator
    Operator that execute a division with the two parameter This operator need number before and after the symbol "/" Exemple : 30 / 6 = 5 -3 / 2 = -1.5
    EqualsOperator
    Operator that check if the right parameter is equals to the left parameter This operator work with number, strings or boolean before and after the symbol "==" Exemple: 6 == 6 = true 6 == 5 = false true == false = false "I love ewoks" == "I hate ewoks" = false
    GreaterOrEqualsThanOperator
    Operator that return true if the left parameter is greater or equals than the right parameter, false if it is not.
    GreaterThanOperator
    Operator that return true if the left parameter is greater than the right parameter, false if it is not.
    InjectorOperator  
    InstructionEndOperator
    Operator that separate operation instruction and return the last instruction
    This operator can be used between any operation with the symbol ";"
    Exemple:
    echo I love ; echo ewok = ewok
    echo I hate (echo ewok ; echo wookies) = I hate wookies
    LowerOrEqualsThanOperator
    Operator that return true if the left parameter is lower or equals than the right parameter, false if it is not.
    LowerThanOperator
    Operator that return true if the left parameter is lower than the right parameter, false if it is not.
    MinusOperator
    Operator that execute a subtraction with the two parameter This operator need number before and after the symbol "-" Exemple : 5 - 6 = -1 -3 - 2 = -5
    ModuloOperator
    Operator that return the values of the left parameter modulo the right one.
    MultiplicationOperator
    Operator that execute a multiplication with the two parameter This operator need number before and after the symbol "*" Exemple : 5 * 6 = 30 -3 * 2 = -6
    NotOperator
    Operator that return the opposite of the given parameter.
    OrOperator
    Operator that return true if the left or right parameter are true, false if both are false.
    ParenthesesOperator  
    PlusOperator
    Operator that execute an addition with the two parameter This operator need number before and after the symbol "+" Exemple : 5 + 6 = 11 -3 + 2 = -1
    PowerOperator
    Operator that raise the left parameter to the power of the right parameter.
    SkipOperator
    Operator that replace the instruction by a none interpretable value.
    This operator work with any operation instruction between the symbols simples quotes (" ' ")
    Exemple:
    'echo I love ewok' = echo I love ewok
    'I love ewoks' = I love ewoks
    XorOperator
    Operator that return true if at least one of the parameter is true, false if both are false or both are true.
